         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Melbourne, ¶ 9/2/84. ¶ The honorable Graham Berry, M.L.A., ¶ Chief Secretary. ¶ Sir,...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">84.02.09a</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Graham Berry</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">A84/1448, unit 21, VPRS 3992/P inward registered correspondence, VA 475 Chief Secretary's Department, Public Record Office, Victoria.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Melbourne,</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">9/2/84.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">The honorable Graham Berry, M.L.A.,</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Chief Secretary.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Sir,</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I have the honor to forward herewith an application addressed to me by Mr. Charles French,<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Charles French Snr; see C. French to M, 8 February 1884<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(in this edition as 84-02-08a).</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>who is eager to fill the situation, which became vacant by the death of Mr. Charles Groener. As for ten years Mr. French was engaged under me in the botanic Gardens, I learnt to recognize his ability and zeal and general excellent character; and as he has a very extensive knowledge of plants<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>and an usual<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>unusual?</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>aptitude<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>for museum work (splendidly exemplified at the Melbourne International Exhibition) he would be singularly fitted to perform the duties, which in the position rendered vacant would devolve on him.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn2" n="3">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>T. Wilson, Under Secretary, sent the file to M on 13 February, seeking further information: 'The Government Botanist is requested to state: —</p>
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>(1) What were the precise duties respectively devolving on the late Mr Groener and the other assistants whose services are paid for out of the vote Divn 13/2 Books Wages &amp;c</p>
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>(2) What are the names, present duties, length of service and wages of Mr French and the other persons now employed and paid out of the Incidental Vote of his Department.'</p>
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>For M's reply, see M to T. Wilson, 14 February 1884.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">I have the honor to be,</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Sir, your obedient servant</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller.</p>
         </div>
